               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="RAS_Persian_271-item1">
                     <author key="person_259934160" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/259934160/" change="#ids-cleanup">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Ḥāfiẓ, 14th cent.</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Ḥāfiẓ Shīrāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Shams al-Dīn Muḥammad Shīrāzī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">‏حافظ شيرازى</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_20666" change="#ids-cleanup">Dīvān-i Ḥāfiẓ</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_20666" change="#ids-cleanup">دیوان حافظ</title>
                     <note>Inside front cover, armorial bookplate of Gordon of Buthlaw. F1a: impression of circular seal of the slave of the House of Muhammad, Muhammad ... Khaliqi, the date illegible. Folio preceding text, verso: impression of circular seal of Mustafa ...? The edges of the pages decorated in gold. A manuscript of good quality. Ruled blue and gold margins and dividing panels. In a panel above each poem the attribution is confirmed, in gold and blue alternately. Small panel of illumination above text.</note>
                     <incipit>Ala ya ayyuha 'l-saqi</incipit>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>As for Codrington/Reade No 265.</bibl>
                        <bibl>General Gordon's bequest of books and Turkish, Perian and Arabic manuscripts is mentioned, without details in the donations register under November 6 1841. The bequest is mentioned in J.R.A.S., vii, 1843, Annual Report, p. x, and the manuscripts are briefly listed in the Proceedings, pp. xxx-xxxi.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian.</textLang>
                  </msItem>
               </msContents>
